  "decision_conditions": [
    "CONDITION:  All new facing brickwork shall match the existing brickwork adjacent with regard to colour, texture, face bond and pointing and the brickwork shall be maintained as such thereafter.\r\n\r\nThe new sash windows shall accurately replicate the surviving historic windows in terms of material, profile, reveal depth and detailing.  The windows shall be painted timber, double-hung sash windows without horns, with a slim profile and narrow integral glazing bars with a putty finish.  \r\n\r\nAll new slates shall be natural.\r\n\r\nREASON:  In order to safeguard the special architectural or historic interest of the heritage asset in accordance with policy 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2012, policy D24 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002 and policy CS9A and B of the Islington Core Strategy 2011."
